25/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- European Commissioner for Employment and Social Affairs Anna Diamantopoulou urged Bulgarian authorities to solve problems related to human trafficking, protection of children's and handicapped people's rights, adopting laws as needed. 
Diamantopoulou met on Tuesday (24 June) met with Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov about the social aspects of EU integration. 
For his part, Parvanov pointed out to the achievements made so far and reiterated Bulgaria's commitment to meet integration obligations. 
(Dnevnik, Trud, Sega - 25/06/03; BTA - 24/06/03)
